        Keuper—characteristic of central European strata. These units typify the
        tripartite stratigraphy of the period in terrestrial and shallow marine
        depositional environments, reflecting a complex interplay of climatic and
        tectonic regimes during the initial Mesozoic.  Stratigraphically, the Triassic
