        severe Phanerozoic mass extinction—and the Triassic-Jurassic boundary atop, both
        global events that significantly affected biotic assemblages and sedimentation.
        This interval witnessed the gradual recovery and radiation of ecosystems,
        including the earliest diversification of dinosaurs, ichthyosaurs, and marine
        reptiles, as well as the proliferation of gymnosperms and the origin of modern
        conifers. The Triassic climatic regime varied from arid continental interiors to
        monsoonal patterns, influenced by the supercontinent Pangaea’s configuration.
