        elucidating the evolutionary and environmental processes that shaped subsequent
        Mesozoic biotas and paleogeography. It records the rebound from the most
        catastrophic extinction event, setting the stage for the rise of dominant
        vertebrate clades and intricate terrestrial ecosystems, thereby providing vital
        insights into biotic resilience, adaptation, and large-scale geodynamic
        transitions.
