            and environmental transition. As the terminal Triassic stage, it records
            critical patterns of species extinctions, climatic fluctuations, and biotic
            recovery processes. Consequently, the Rhaetian is fundamental for understanding
            the interplay between tectonics, climate, and biotic evolution at a major
            Phanerozoic boundary and remains a focal point for geochronological and
