            significant tectonic and volcanic activity, influencing sedimentation patterns
            and paleoenvironmental conditions.  Understanding the Norian stage is pivotal
            because it captures a period of evolutionary innovation and ecosystem
            restructuring preceding the end-Triassic extinction. Its well-preserved fossil
            record serves as an essential framework for reconstructing palaeobiogeographic
