            transition.  The Carnian is particularly significant for its association with
            the “Carnian Pluvial Episode” (CPE), an interval of increased humidity and
            climatic upheaval that catalyzed major biotic turnovers across marine and
            terrestrial ecosystems. This event is linked to volcanic activity, basin
            transgressions, and pivotal evolutionary radiations, notably among early
            dinosaurs and modern conifer groups. Therefore, the Carnian serves as a
            geochronological window for understanding both climatic perturbations and faunal
