            diversifications within the Olenekian underpin the establishment of Early
            Triassic evolutionary trajectories.  Understanding the Olenekian stage is vital
            for elucidating the mechanisms and tempo of ecosystem recovery from acute
            extinction stress. It provides a window into Early Triassic ocean chemistry,
            climatic upheavals, and biotic rediversification, offering insights into
            resilience and adaptability patterns within marine and terrestrial realms.
