        extinction series, which reshaped marine biodiversity patterns.  The Devonian’s
        importance lies in its encapsulation of critical evolutionary and
        paleoenvironmental shifts that laid the foundation for subsequent terrestrial
        ecosystems and vertebrate radiation. Its record provides invaluable insights
        into early vertebrate evolution, paleoclimate dynamics, and reef ecosystem
        development, making the Devonian an essential period for understanding Paleozoic
