      ago, constitutes the middle subdivision of the Proterozoic Eon. The term
      "Mesoproterozoic" derives from the Greek μέσος (mesos), meaning “middle,”
      combined with "Proterozoic," denoting the “earlier life” eon characterized by
      the emergence of increasingly complex organisms. This era occupies a crucial
      stratigraphic interval between the earlier Paleo- and later Neoproterozoic
