        elucidating the tectonothermal events that shaped the continental lithosphere
        and influenced biogeochemical cycles.  The Ectasian period matters
        scientifically as it encapsulates fundamental Earth system evolutions, including
        enhanced oxygenation episodes and the diversification of eukaryotic life. The
        tectonic reconfigurations during this time modulated sediment flux and nutrient
