        thickening and recycling of older crust, contributing to the stabilization of
        the continental lithosphere. Additionally, the period witnessed significant
        magmatic and metamorphic activity, preserved within well-exposed
        Paleoproterozoic terrains. Sedimentary successions from this time provide
        critical data on atmospheric and oceanic conditions, reflecting evolving Earth
        surface environments amidst the Great Oxidation Event’s aftermath.  The
        Orosirian’s importance lies in its encapsulation of Earth’s transition from
        Archean geodynamics to more modern plate tectonics, with implications for
