        atmospheric changes like the rise in oxygen levels during the Great Oxidation
        Event. These factors collectively underscore the Rhyacian as a pivotal period in
        Earth's geobiological evolution, informing understanding of early biosphere-
        environment interactions, continental crust maturation, and the interplay of
        tectonics and climate in the Paleoproterozoic.
