      provide insights into early magmatic differentiation.  The Paleoarchean is
      pivotal for understanding the transition from a predominantly mafic crust to
      more felsic compositions, indicating early plate tectonics or analogous
      processes that involved crustal recycling and growth. Moreover, it coincides
      with the earliest geochemical signatures suggestive of life, such as isotopic
      fractionations in carbonates and sedimentary rocks, thereby informing models of
      early biosphere development and environmental conditions. The study of
